    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files:
                    Lot 63D351: <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68 Series</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Report to the National Security Council by the Executive
                        Secretary</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-30">September 30,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/2</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Note by the Executive Secretary to the National Security
                        Council on United States Objectives and Programs for National Security</hi>
                </p>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>References: A. <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 361<note
                                n="1" xml:id="d129fn1">The substance of <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                                    >NSC</gloss> Action No. 361 is contained in the present
                                report.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>B. <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68;<note n="2" xml:id="d129fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_234">p.
                                234</ref>.</note>
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/1; Annexes to <gloss
                                target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/1<note n="3" xml:id="d129fn3">
                                <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/1, “United States Objectives
                                and Programs for National Security,” a report to the National
                                Security Council by the Executive Secretary, September 21, and its
                                annexes, are not printed. For revisions thereof, see <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/3 and its annexes, December 8
                                (extracts), <ref target="#pg_425">pp. 425</ref> and <ref
                                    target="#pg_432">432</ref>, respectively, and <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/4, December 14, <ref
                                    target="#pg_467">p. 467</ref>.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>C. <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 20/4<note n="4"
                                xml:id="d129fn4">See footnote 3, <ref target="#pg_359">p.
                                359</ref>.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>At the 68th Council meeting, with the President presiding (<gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 361), the National Security Council,
                    the Secretary of the Treasury, the Secretary of Commerce, the Acting Economic
                    Cooperation Administrator, the Director, Bureau of the Budget, and the Chairman,
                    Council of Economic Advisers, considered draft reports on “United States
                    Objectives and Programs for National Security” (<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 68 and <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/1), and:</p>
                <list>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                    <item>Adopted the Conclusions of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68 as a
                        statement of policy to be followed over the next four or five years, and
                        agreed that the implementing programs will be put into effect as rapidly as
                        feasible, with the understanding that the specific nature and estimated
                        costs of these programs will be decided as they are more firmly
                        developed.</item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                    <item>Deferred action on <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68/1 pending a
                        revision of that report to be prepared by the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Staff for Council consideration not later than November 15,
                        1950.</item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                    <item>Noted the President’s instructions that there should be no public
                        discussion of this program, and specifically no public quotation of figures,
                        until the appropriate time as determined by the President.</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has this date approved the Conclusions of <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 68 as a statement of policy to be followed over the next four
                    or five years, and directed their implementation by all appropriate executive
                    departments and agencies of the U.S. Government.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, the Conclusions of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 68 are
                    circulated herewith for appropriate action.<note n="5" xml:id="d129fn5">The
                        enclosure consists of the conclusions of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                        68, April 14, <ref target="#pg_234">p. 234</ref>, with a small number of
                        minor variations in form.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay,
                        Jr</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
